It was the Thursday afternoon of Spring Break and the Blue Devils were planning to play Florida State the next day.
“At that point for me, it was just a matter of enjoying the presence of my best friends,” Wilson said.
For the Blue Devils, the virus cut short their best start to a season in the young program’s history.
In the final USA Today/Coaches poll of the season, Duke received the most votes of any team outside the top-25.
“For me, that’s the toughest part, not being able to see that through.”But it’s a young program and a young team, and the future looks bright.